W. H. BELCHER, D. ORVILL HARRIS, JOHN CHESNUT, ANDREW E. POTTER AND ED H. BECKETT as and constituting The Board of County Commissioners of Pinellas County, Florida, v. STATE OF FLORIDA EX REL. FRANK J. McNULTY. 32 So. (2nd) 282

June Term, 1947

October 24, 1947 En Banc McMullen, McMullen & Pogue, Carey & Harrison and Archie Clement, for appellant. James Booth, Leonard Cooperman, William Kaleel, William Gardner and Robert Barton, for Appellee. PER CURIAM:

Affirmed on authority of our opinion and judgment in Prince et al. v. State ex rel. Williams, 157 Fla. 103, 25 So. (2nd) 5.

So ordered.

THOMAS, C. J., TERRELL, BUFORD, CHAPMAN, SE-BRING and BARNS, JJ., concur.
